123

Growing on the interior of large burned out Northern Red Oak on mixed oak/hickory ridgetop in woodland. 
- In close proximity to Trichaptum biforme and Fuscoporia gilva.
- Upper cap, and hymenium slowly bruising olive green.

- Hymenophore with copious amount of guttation, even for how dry weather conditions have been recently.
